."},{"title":"Division by Zero in Health Factor Calculation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"False positive. The zero-collateral case is explicitly handled, and the shown code path does not divide by zero."},{"title":"No Access Control on initialize Function After First Initialization","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"False positive. `initializer` prevents repeated calls, and front-running `Pool.initialize` does not seize privileges or change the immutable provider."},{"title":"Integer Overflow in Isolation Mode Debt Calculation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"False positive. Solidity 0.8 checked arithmetic plus `SafeCast` and bounded debt-ceiling storage prevent silent truncation/overflow here."},{"title":"Missing Validation for Debt Ceiling in Isolation Mode","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"A large debt ceiling chosen by governance is a risk-parameter decision, not a code vulnerability by itself."}]}
